##Your company accounts

You must send amended accounts to Companies House on paper. 

You must follow [specific rules for revised accounts.](http://www.companieshouse.gov.uk/infoAndGuide/faq/amendingAccounts.shtml "Revised (amending) accounts FAQs"){:rel="external"}

##Your Company Tax Return

You must usually do this within 12 months of the filing deadline.

You can:

- amend your [Company Tax Return online](http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/ct/managing/company-tax-return/amend.htm "How to amend your Company Tax Return online"){:rel="external"}
- write to your company's HM Revenue & Customs (HMRC) [Corporation Tax office](http://search2.hmrc.gov.uk/kbroker/hmrc/locator/locator.jsp?type=0 "Find your Corporation Tax office"){:rel="external"}

If you made an error, you should correct it as soon as possible. HMRC may charge you a penalty for errors.

*[HMRC]: HM Revenue & Customs
